---
import RelayStatusPanel from "../../components/RelayStatusPanel.vue";
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="bore | relay operator status"
  description="Read-only relay status, served same-origin from the Go relay and refreshed in the browser without a separate Python runtime."
>
  <section class="two-up">
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Operator-facing surface</p>
      <h1>Relay status, without pretending it is a control plane.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        This page reads aggregate service data from the current relay at
        <code>/status</code>. The relay serves as a signaling server for direct
        peer-to-peer setup and as a fallback transport when direct connection fails.
      </p>
      <p>
        The scope stays read-only: uptime, room counts, signaling activity, and
        configured limits. No auth UI. No writes. No hidden backend.
      </p>
    </article>
    <aside class="panel panel--aside">
      <p class="eyebrow">Current scope</p>
      <p>
        The relay remains payload-blind. It coordinates direct connection setup and
        forwards encrypted bytes only when the direct path does not hold.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the terminal lane today, <code>bore-admin status</code> reads the same
        contract. A dedicated TUI belongs to a later phase.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <RelayStatusPanel client:load />
</BaseLayout>
